  "prompt": "What are some small restaurant chains in Dallas? (under 10 locations)",
  "response": "Dallas is home to several small, locally-owned restaurant chains, each with fewer than 10 locations. These eateries often focus on unique concepts, regional flavors, and strong community ties. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n### 1. **Velvet Taco**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Creative tacos with global influences  \n   - **Locations**: 6 in Dallas (as of 2023)  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Known for its bold flavors and unconventional taco combinations, like the Nashville hot chicken taco or the falafel taco.\n\n### 2. **Hopdoddy Burger Bar** (Dallas-based locations)  \n   - **Cuisine**: Gourmet burgers and craft beer  \n   - **Locations**: 5 in Dallas  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Offers hand-crafted burgers, fresh buns baked in-house, and a curated selection of craft beers.\n\n### 3. **Bread Winners Caf\u00e9 & Bakery**  \n   - **Cuisine**: American comfort food with a Southern twist  \n   - **Locations**: 4 in Dallas  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Famous for its brunch menu, fresh pastries, and cozy atmosphere.\n\n### 4. **Lockhart Smokehouse**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Texas-style barbecue  \n   - **Locations**: 2 in Dallas (Plano and Bishop Arts District)  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: A family-owned BBQ joint with roots in Lockhart, TX, serving up brisket, sausages, and ribs.\n\n### 5. **Cane Rosso**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Authentic Neapolitan pizza  \n   - **Locations**: 7 in the Dallas-Fort Worth area (including Dallas)  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Wood-fired pizzas made with imported Italian ingredients, plus a fun, casual vibe.\n\n### 6. **Rusty Taco**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Simple, street-style tacos  \n   - **Locations**: 6 in Dallas  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Affordable, no-frills tacos with a variety of fillings in a relaxed setting.\n\n### 7. **HG Sply Co.**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Healthy, farm-to-table American food  \n   - **Locations**: 2 in Dallas (Lower Greenville and Preston Center)  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Focuses on clean, sustainable ingredients with a rooftop bar offering great views.\n\n### 8. **The Crab Station**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Seafood boils and Cajun-style dishes  \n   - **Locations**: 3 in Dallas  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: A no-fuss spot for seafood lovers, offering customizable boils with a variety of sauces and spices.\n\n### 9. **Whiskey Cake**  \n   - **Cuisine**: American farm-to-table cuisine  \n   - **Locations**: 2 in Dallas (Plano and Irving)  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Known for its seasonal menus, craft cocktails, and signature whiskey cake dessert.\n\n### 10. **Tribal All Day Caf\u00e9**  \n   - **Cuisine**: Coffee shop and caf\u00e9 with global influences  \n   - **Locations**: 1 in Dallas (with plans to expand)  \n   - **Why it\u2019s unique**: Combines coffee culture with a diverse menu featuring dishes like shakshuka and Korean fried chicken.\n\nThese small chains offer a mix of flavors and experiences, making them great spots to explore the local Dallas dining scene.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
